Create a simple web application (HTML or Python Flask). Write a Dockerfile, build a Docker
image, and run the container so the application is accessible on a browser using port mapping.
Using Docker commands, perform the following operations:
List images and containers
Stop a running container
Remove a container and image
Demonstrate commands like: docker ps, docker stop, docker rm, docker rmi

mkdir appDocker
cd appDocker

gedit index.html:
<h1> docker running</h1>

gedit Dockerfile:
FROM nginx:latest
COPY index.html /usr/share/nginx/html

docker --version
sudo apt update
sudo apt install docker.io -y
sudo systemctl start docker
sudo systemctl enable docker
docker --version
sudo docker build -t html-app:1.0 .
docker images
docker run -d -p 8081:80 html-app:1.0
docker ps
docker stop container_id
docker rm container_id
docker rmi image_name






